In answer, we ask, first .· Since it is as certain that Christ did not eat sitting or standing, as that he did not eat kneeling3 why are we not as much obliged by his example to abstain from sitting or standing as from kneeling? Of these three postures, each is as un- supported by the example of Christ as the other two. All the three stand on like grounds.

They reply, that reclining has, by the custom of society, been succeeded by sitting, and has not been succeeded by kneeling.
